snippet.textDisplay:
This has been a great season and we expected some songs to be better then others. DT is a great composition and which has become tarana for peace for people of India and Pakistan...and with Salman on guitar music was great and song was great. However Ghoom Taana    was sung by Shubha Mudgal and Salman Ahmed and made it a anthem  and burned the tapes. I can still hear it playing it in my head. Here we have thrown Momina in the river without a life jacket and equally helpless was Irtesh....This composition made me appreciate what a great musician he is. 
However this season  has seem too many bad pairings that have not done justice to some  songs and those songs didn't create the magic as  expected. Going from Shubha M to Momina  was a great stretch. They still made it wonderful but imagine if we had Hina Nusrullah, Sanam Marvi, Masuma Anwar and Abida Parveen singing this song then imagine where this song could have gone.
We need to continue the journey of bringing in our unique talents like Shafqat Ali Khan for  Multani Kafi   w  S Bagga could be great experiment.
